---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Coderturtle">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-mono text-green-700">Welcome to Coderturtle 🐢</h1>
  <p class="mt-4 text-lg mb-10">Architecting one shell at a time.</p>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">🧠 Coderturtle’s Current Shell Stack</h2>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Obsidian + Astro</strong> – writing blogs in Markdown like it’s a spiritual practice.</li>
      <li><strong>Terraform</strong> – for when you want to spin up the cloud and break it immediately.</li>
      <li><strong>OpenAI GPT + Prompt Engineering</strong> – the new IDE of weird ideas.</li>
      <li><strong>Next.js for Docs</strong> – building turtles inside turtles.</li>
      <li><strong>Comics-as-Architecture-Diagrams</strong> – technically a diagram if you squint hard enough.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>
</Layout>
